ckchain or other Monitor regulatory and reputational components inclusive of new or pending regulation Provide support for reviewing technology initiatives identified during defined intake procedures Prepare the Technology Risk report to the Risk Committee of the Board and track actions to reduce technology risk Assist with the technology risk reporting operations, including scheduling key monthly meetings, monitoring milestones, escalation of past due activities, problem triage and management and archiving key monthly artifacts for audit purposes Develop ongoing technology risk reporting, monitoring key trends and defining metrics to regularly measure control effectiveness for the business area Adhere to internal policies and procedures, technology control standards and applicable regulatory guidelines Contribute to the review of internal processes and activities and assist in identifying potential opportunities for improvement Adhere to, advise, oversee, monitor and enforce enterprise frameworks and methodologies that relate to technology controls / information security activities Influence behavior to reduce risk and foster a strong technology risk management culture throughout the enterprise Develop and maintain a system of risk management for technology related issues: Create and manage metrics and key risk indicators to effectively measure leading and lagging indicators of risk Identify the risk impacts of individual projects on Technology\u2019s overall risk levels Align controls across different frameworks such as the Payment Card Industry, Digital Security Standard, NIST or other. Track gaps and deficiencies in controls and monitor remediation plans as well as their ability to counter risk Communicate and report risk levels meaningfully to drive action: Report risk levels and key actions to mitigate risk to senior leadership and the Risk Committee of the Board Raise awareness and areas of concern to technology executives to drive action plans Work closely with technical delivery teams to implement risk mitigating solutions Requirements Degree or diploma from a recognized post secondary institution in a technology or other quantitative discipline A minimum of 5 years experience in managing risks in a medium or large enterprise with financial services experience as an asset A minimum of 5 years experience in a leadership role overseeing direct reports. Knowledge of key technology architectural concepts and control frameworks Strong analytical and critical thinking skills with demonstrated capacity for problem solving, synthesis, and making sound recommendations and decisions Proven ability to create reporting and communications for senior management and board level audiences, especially as it relates to translating technology into simple business terms. Proven ability to lead and grow teams Ability to negotiate, influence, collaborate and build strong working relationships with partners and stakeholders. Excellent verbal and written communication skills with the ability to deliver technical issues to both technical and non-technical audiences in a clear and understandable manner At ATB, we know that highly talented people can readily transfer their skills. If you believe your skills and experience are transferable, please consider putting your name in the running. Online applications are preferred. Benefits Purpose. Growth. Advancement. Fun. Rewards\u2026 learn about our perks and benefits. A little about ATB: We are Alberta\u2019s largest, home grown financial institution and for the last 80+ years, we\u2019ve transformed people\u2019s understanding of what banking can\u2013and should\u2013make possible. Today, 5,500+ ATB team members embrace a growth mindset in order to help bring ATB\u2019s story to life, delivering happiness to our customers and team members alike. It\u2019s why we\u2019re also a highly sought after, award-winning employer. The best part is, we\u2019re just getting started. Join us, and create happi